hackathon-description-text: StacsHack 2016 is St Andrews' biggest student technology event. Over the course of the weekend, 130+ student makers from St Andrews and beyond will form teams to develop their ideas and present projects built over 24 hours! Join us for an incredible weekend of hacking, free food, mini-events, and prizes for the best ideas! Last year, we hosted over 100 hackers from 10 universities creating fantastic projects such as virtual reality games, sign language training apps and smart-home automation systems.
